   CORPORATE-LOGOS (Undated) _ Corporate logos are supposed to be
universal and unchanging, their color, size and placement spelled
out in corporate-image policy books. From the International
Business Machines Corporation to Federal Express, the power to
imprint everything from a headquarters building to business cards
has been a sign of corporate efficiency and organization, implying
a power and dependability customers could trust. But lately logos
show signs of softening up and growing more playful. By Phil
Patton.
