<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OUT-FISHDAY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FISH DAY COMING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRETT PAULY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Saturday marks not only California's biannual Free
Fishing Day, when an angling license _ normally a $27.55 charge per
year _ is not required to target state waters, but national and
state Hunting and Fishing Day.
</P>
<P>
   Local anglers can celebrate by taking part in a family fishing
derby and festival slated from 8 a.m. to 2 p.m. at El Dorado Park
Lake, 7550 E. Spring St. in Long Beach.
</P>
<P>
   More than 4,000 half-pound channel catfish will be planted by
the Department of Fish and Game, and volunteers will man
learn-to-fish stations and offer tips on technique and lessons in
fish biology. Loaners rods and reels are available; personal ID is
required. Complimentary bait, hooks and sinkers are also to be
provided.
</P>
<P>
   The festival will include nature exhibits, animal displays,
train rides and pedal boats.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, call (562) 570-1771 or (562) 590-4835. For
a list of additional lakes and streams that will be planted prior
to Free Fishing Day, phone the DFG's fish-stocking report, (562)
590-5020.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Gov. Pete Wilson on Sept. 10 proclaimed Sept. 26
Hunting and Fishing Day to honor the contributions hunters and
anglers have made to the conservation of habitat and species
through the purchase of licenses and special taxes on equipment
they use. The fourth Saturday in September has been recognized as
National Hunting and Fishing Day since then-president Richard Nixon
designated it as such in 1972.
</P>
<P>
   Locally, one NHFD event (albeit a day late) is planned:
</P>
<P>
   __ The Santa Clarita Valley chapter of Quail Unlimited and
Claybuster Trap Club will host a fun shoot from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m.
Sunday at the Oak Tree Gun Club, 23121 N. Coltrane Ave. in Newhall.
</P>
<P>
   Cost is $32 and includes a 100-target format, trophies for top
shooters and a barbecue lunch. Information: (805) 297-0876, ext. 3,
or (805) 259-7441.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
