<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NETHAWAY-COLUMN25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Republicans &AMP; Democrats
 &HT;    By Rowland Nethaway
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WACO, Texas _ With the Republicans and Democrats shamelessly
tearing at each other's throats in Washington, it's good to recall
the fundamental differences between these distinct political
species.
</P>
<P>
   The following list from the Sterling Bulletin was compiled long
before Bill Clinton invented New Democrats, which is makes
identification more difficult.
</P>
<P>
   Some of these identification hints need to be updated. Some are
still valid.
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats buy most of the books that have been banned
somewhere. Republicans form censorship committees and read them in
a group.
</P>
<P>
   (This one can be updated by noting that Republicans are the ones
who release prurient material for public consumption when the
prurience is committed by Democrats.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans consume three-fourths of all the rutabaga produced
in this country. The remainder is thrown out.
</P>
<P>
   (This hint is still valid.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans usually wear hats and almost always clean their
paintbrushes.
</P>
<P>
   (Only the part about the paintbrushes remains helpful today.)
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats give their worn-out clothes to those less fortunate.
Republicans wear theirs.
</P>
<P>
   (Now both parties give their worn-out clothes to the less
fortunate, but only Republicans take the tax deduction.)
_Republicans employ exterminators. Democrats step on the bugs.
</P>
<P>
   (Some things never change.)
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats name their children after currently popular sports
figures, politicians and entertainers. Republican children are
named after their parents or grandparents, according to where the
most money is.
</P>
<P>
   (A lasting difference.)
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats keep trying to cut down on smoking, but are not
successful. Neither are Republicans.
</P>
<P>
   (The difference now is that Republicans solicit money from Big
Tobacco, and the Democrats take it only when it is offered.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans tend to keep their shades drawn, although there is
seldom any reason why they should. Democrats ought to, but don't.
</P>
<P>
   (Now both Republicans and Democrats keep their shades drawn, but
never enough since both window-peep on each other and tattle.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans study the financial pages of the newspaper.
Democrats put them in the bottom of the bird cage.
</P>
<P>
   (Birds aren't as popular as they once were.)
</P>
<P>
   _Most of the stuff you see alongside the road has been thrown
out of car windows by Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   (Still true, but most of the superfund cleanup sites were caused
by Republicans.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans raise dahlias, Dalmatians and eyebrows. Democrats
raise Airedales, kids and taxes.
</P>
<P>
   (Forget the dogs.)
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats eat the fish they catch. Republicans hang them on the
wall.
</P>
<P>
   (Democrats now own the most expensive bass boats.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republican boys date Democrat girls. They plan to marry
Republican girls, but feel they're entitled to a little fun first.
</P>
<P>
   (A truism.)
</P>
<P>
   _Democrats make up plans and then do something else. Republicans
follow the plans their grandfathers made.
</P>
<P>
   (An old mainstay.)
</P>
<P>
   _Republicans sleep in twin beds _ some even in separate rooms.
That is why there are more Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   (Republicans have done a lot of sleepwalking in recent years.)
</P>
<P>
   Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco (Texas)
Tribune-Herald. E-mail: RNethaol.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
