<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: ACADIANA 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By HARRY SHATTUCK 
and SYD KEARNEY 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ADVANCE PLANNING
</P>
<P>
   _ The Lafayette Convention and Visitors Bureau can supply
brochures that cover that city and beyond. Call 800-346-1958; or
access http://www.lafayettetravel.com on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Louisiana Department of Culture, Recreation and Tourism
publishes brochures about Acadiana and statewide attractions. Call
800-633-6970; or access http://www.louisianatravel.com.
</P>
<P>
   _ Among other good resources: Vermilion Parish Tourist
Commission in Abbeville, 318-898-6600; Iberia Parish Tourist
Commission in New Iberia, 888-942-3742; St. Landry Parish Tourist
Commission in Opelousas, 800-424-5442; and St. Martinville Tourist
Commission, 318-394-2233.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR;  &QL; 
 &LR; LODGING &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ The 337-room Lafayette Hilton and Towers, situated on the
banks of Bayou Vermilion a short drive from downtown, represents a
good base for exploring the region. A Sunday jazz brunch is served
in the hotel's restaurant. Call 800-332-2586 or 318-235-6111. Or
contact a travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   _ Six-room leRosier in New Iberia is one of the most comfortable
small inns we've visited. Its restaurant is widely acclaimed.
Shadows-on-the-Teche, an 1834 plantation home operated by the
National Trust for Historic Preservation, is directly across East
Main Street. Call 888-804-7673 or 318-367-5306.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chretien Point Plantation is an 1830s mansion converted into a
bed-and-breakfast about a 30-minute drive north of Lafayette in the
countryside near Sunset. It features comfortable rooms and warm
hospitality. (Tours are conducted daily for visitors who don't stay
overnight.) Call 800-880-7050 or 318-662-5876. Ask for directions.
</P>
<P>
   _ Numerous other hotels and motels, B&AMP;Bs and about 1,000
campground sites are located in the Lafayette area. The Convention
and Visitors Bureau can provide details.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL; 
 &LR; ATTRACTIONS &QL; 
(Note: All times are CDT) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ The Jean Lafitte National Historical Park and Acadian Culture
Center, at 501 Fisher Road in Lafayette, is open 10 a.m.-5 p.m.
daily. Admission is free. Call 318-232-0789.
</P>
<P>
   _ Vermilionville, a living history museum and village at 1600
Surrey St. in Lafayette, is open 10 a.m.-5 p.m. daily. Admission is
$8, with discounts for seniors and students. Call 800-992-2968 or
318-233-4077.
</P>
<P>
   _ Acadian Village, accessed via West Broussard Street in
Lafayette, is open 10 a.m.- 5 p.m. daily. Admission is $6. Call
800-962-9133 or 318-981-2489.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Children's Museum of Acadiana, at 201 E. Congress in
downtown Lafayette, is open 10 a.m.-5 p.m. Tuesdays-Saturdays. Call
318-232-8500.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Alexandre Mouton House/Lafayette Museum is the former home
of Jean Mouton, founder of Lafayette. The museum is located at 1122
Lafayette St. and is open 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Tuesday-Saturday and 3-5
p.m. Sunday. Admission is $3, with discounts for seniors and
students. Call 318-234-2208.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Lafayette Natural History Museum and Planetarium, at 637
Girard Park in Lafayette, is open 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Monday through
Friday (until 9 p.m. on Tuesday) and 1-5 p.m. on weekends. Call
318-291-5544; inquire about times for planetarium shows and
telescope viewing.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Zoo of Acadiana, at 116 Lakeview Drive in Broussard, is
open 9 a.m.-5 p.m. daily. Admission is $6.95, with discounts for
children. Call 318-837-4325.
</P>
<P>
   _ Shadows-on-the-Teche, at 317 E. Main St. in New Iberia, is
open 9 a.m.-4:30 p.m. daily (except some holidays). Guided tours
and lectures are scheduled. Admission is $6, with discounts for
young children. Call 318-369-6446.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Liberty Theater, at the corner of Second Street and Park
Avenue, hosts its two-hour French-speaking radio and television
show 6-8 p.m. Saturdays. Admission is $3. Call 318-457-7389.
</P>
<P>
   _ McGee's Landing and Atchafalaya Basin Tours is located on the
Henderson Levee Road in Breaux Bridge. Tours depart 8 a.m., 10
a.m., 1 p.m. and 3 p.m. daily February through December. Admission
is $12 ($6 for children). Call 800-445-6681.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Tabasco Country Store and Visitor Center on Avery Island
is open 9 a.m.-4 p.m. Mondays-Fridays and 9 a.m.-noon. Saturdays.
Self-guided factory tours are available. Admission is free. Call
318-365-8173.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jungle Gardens, with its nationally acclaimed bird sanctuary,
is located near the Tabasco factory on Avery Island. Hours are 8
a.m.-5:30 p.m. daily. Admission is $5.50. Call 318-369-6243.
</P>
<P>
   _ Rip Van Winkle Gardens, set on 25 acres on Jefferson Island
south of Lafayette, is open 9 a.m.-5 p.m. daily (except some
holidays). Several ticket packages are available. Call
318-365-3332.
</P>
<P>
   _ Le Petit Paris Museum, 103 S. Main St. in St. Martinville, is
open 9:30 a.m.-4:30 p.m. daily. Admission is $1 (50 cents for
children). Call 318-394-7334.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Evangeline Oak is located in Evangeline Oak Park in St.
Martinville. An adjacent visitor's center is open 10 a.m.-4 p.m.
Free admission. Call 318-394-2233.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Acadian Memorial is located on New Market Street across
from City Hall in St. Martinville. The memorial is open daily.
Admission is free, but a donation is suggested. Call 318-394-2258.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Wortman Pottery Showroom and studio, located at 1769
Potters Road between Duson and Rayne, are open from 10 a.m.-6 p.m.
Wednesday through Saturday or by appointment. Call 318-873-8584.
</P>
<P>
   These telephone contacts may also help in planning a trip:
</P>
<P>
   _ Lafayette Art Gallery: 318-269-0363.
</P>
<P>
   _ University Art Museum, Lafayette: 318-482-5326.
</P>
<P>
   _ Prairie Acadian Culture Center, Eunice: 318-457-8499.
</P>
<P>
   _ Acadian Heritage and Cultural Center, Erath: 318-937-5468.
</P>
<P>
   _ Opelousas Museum and Interpretive Center: 318-948-2589.
</P>
<P>
   _ Konriko Company Store, New Iberia: 318-367-6163.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tony Chachere's, Opelousas: 800-551-9066.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Academy of Sacred Heart, second oldest school west of the
Mississippi River (open by appointment only): 318-662-5275.
</P>
<P>
   _ Oaklawn Manor (1830s home), Franklin: 318-828-0434.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
GUIDED TOURS &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   About 20 companies offer area tours by bus, limousine, bicycle
or boat. Specific tours focus on music, history, swamp life or a
combination. The Lafayette Convention and Visitors Bureau can
provide more information.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
`LAGNIAPPE' &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Many Acadiana stores sell CDs, cassettes and videos that feature
Cajun humorists. Murray Conque's cassettes and videos, including
``The Best of Boudreaux'' and ``Thibodeaux,'' can be ordered for
$10 and $20, respectively (plus $2 for shipping), by writing to 129
Tison Road, Carencro, La. 70520.
</P>
