<P>
   SMOG _ U.S. EPA is set today to implement tougher regulations on
nitrogen oxide emissions in 22 states including Ohio. Old,
coal-fired power plants are the chief culprit. Environmental
officials say the regulations, which will require cuts in Nox
levels up to 45 percent in Ohio, are needed to curtail downwind
pollution from the Midwest to the Eastern states. Midwest
politicians and power company officials say the cuts will reduce
electric capacity and hurt the economy. (Dempsey, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 20.
