<P>
   VETERAN-WOMAN-OLDEST-LONG (Undated) Carol Smith. A personal
exploration of the life of Carol's grandmother, Laura Frost Smith,
who, at 105, is believed to be the oldest living American veteran
of World War I. She served as a nurse near the front lines for
several awful months in 1918 _ months that would affect the rest of
her life and extend its effect to her children and grandchildren.
With quotes from her letters home, plus insights into how WWI
changed society in general, especially the roles of women. With
photos by and of Laura Smith from the war. PHOTOS
</P>
