ship. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-ON-THE-ROAD (Undated) _ In the old days, travel meant
getting away. Now it means going, but not getting away. To explore
the Third World may still mean lugging a backpack, but inside it
you can have a trove of high-tech devices that tether you as
securely to the first world as a ball and chain. By Nicholas &QL; 
Kristof.
