<P>
   CALIFORNIA -- CADELE. East Bay representatives lashed out at
Republicans for their handling of the investigation into President
Clinton, saying that the president is being used as a political
whipping boy. Also, they talk about what may happen: Miller, for
one, thinks some sort of congressional compromise will be reached,
thus saving Clinton's presidency. Stricherz
</P>
