   COLORADO -- PARK. (Probable.) Sen. Wayne Allard is attaching an
amendment to the FAA bill that would permanently ban all commercial
flights over Rocky Mountain National Park. At the same time, Allard
is upset over the park's use of helicopters to airlift thousands of
pounds of gravel to repair trails in the park. Zaret
</P>
