<P>
   BELLSOUTH _ Sprint's stock rose 6 points yesterday on continued
rumors that the telecommnications company was looking for a merger
partner. Atlanta's BellSouth is considered to be a possible suitor.
(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   COKE-MEETING _ Coca-Cola Co. fell as much as 1 1/16 to 56 15/16
on the news that it will hold an analysts' meeting Friday before
U.S. markets open. Some expect the company to say it's scaling back
third-quarter and full-year earnings estimates. It derives about
two-thirds of its profit overseas, where economic troubles have cut
earnings of many multinational companies. Coca-Cola wouldn't
elaborate on the nature of the meeting other than to say it would
``update'' analysts on earnings and volume. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   CURRENCY _ When a country devalues its money it's bowing to
economic problems. In doing so it's also seeking the economic
advantage of being able to sell its products more cheaply overseas.
But when a group of countries slice away at their currencies in a
fairly short period they're possibly igniting a trade war, a beggar
thy neighbor round of price cuts. (Chambers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   CIRCUS _ The president and co-founder of Atlanta-based
UniverSoul Circus said the circus will do commercials for Southwest
Airlines under the theme Another Southwest Airlines Freedom Story.
One 30-second spot says ``We've got the best show under the Big Top
and Southwest has the best one over it.'' (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   AOL-SPAM _ America Online reverts to its old marketing tactics
of spamming the planet with discs to launch the newest version of
AOL _ version 4.0.
</P>
<P>
   If you want art, we have some stuff that could be
scannable.(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   PAXSON _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Checking angles on Chicken
Soup, Travel Channel, and sweeps/holiday programming. (Plunkett,
Palm Beach Post) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   INTEL-TEXAS _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Now Austin really has Intel
inside. Intel Corp., the world's largest and richest semiconductor
company, is opening a site in Austin where engineers will design
microprocessors. (Ladendorf, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
