 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TV-PERKINS-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In a season that was supposed to be wall-to-wall
silliness, insanity and intellectual insults, how pleasing it has
been to watch a number of fall pilots roll off the network assembly
line looking polished, promising and even, dare I say, mechanically
daring. The latest series worth at least a three-episode look-see
is ``Buddy Faro'' on CBS. By KEN PARISH PERKINS. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-JUST WRITE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Despite likable characters and performances, ``Just
Write'' just doesn't feel quite right. It seems like a
screenwriter's daydream, one in which he gets the pretty actress,
who's really just a person like everyone else. But it's a daydream
built on a shaky foundation. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-URBAN LEGEND &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It's hard to tell who's dumber at Pendleton College:
the students, who frequently walk alone even though a homicidal
maniac is on the loose; or the faculty, who won't believe that
there's a homicidal maniac on the loose despite overwhelming
evidence and the school's troubled past. The dumbness is part of
``Urban Legend's'' appeal. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-RONIN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Ronin'' has a brisk and merciless pace _ it's like a
movie put together by an assassin. It has its moments, but director
John Frankenheimer boils the ingredients _ action, international
terrorism, desperate men down on their luck _ until it collapses
into a muddled stew. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-PECKER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Writer/director John Waters was disgusting when
disgusting wasn't cool. Before the Pythons were vomiting in
restaurants, before Mel Brooks found flatulence funny and before
the Farrelly Brothers discovered a new kind of hair gel _ the
granddaddy of the gross-out was outdoing them all. And with the
arrival of his latest picture ``Pecker'' this weekend, Waters
proves he can still turn a stomach while getting a laugh. By TODD
CAMP. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F I N A N C I A L &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BOOKS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Quick, name the third-largest single household expense
after the house and the car. A pool? A grand piano? A Jacuzzi? How
about your funeral? The average cost for an adult funeral is a
whopping $7,800, according to the funeral industry. That makes the
funeral business big business. By TERESA MCUSIC. Story has moved in
``f'' financial category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
