<P>
   HURRICANE-GEORGES _ MIAMI _ Southern Florida continued to brace
for the approaching storm on Thursday, as Hurricane Georges
appeared to be taking a sounthernmost track across the Caribbean.
By early morning, the storm _ which was still barely a hurricane _
was skimming the northern coast of Cuba, leaving 50 dead in its
wake in other parts of the Caribbean. Developing. (Emling, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   JOURNAL-HURRICANE _ MIAMI _ In my years of travel as a foreign
correspondent throughout the Caribbean and Latin America, there is
very little that I haven't had to deal with _ from corrupt
dictatorships to drug cartels to starving people to tony tourist
meccas. But I'm not sure any of that prepared me for the high
anxiety and paranoia that has gripped this city since it learned
that Hurricance Georges could come its doorstep. (Emling, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   STORM _ The storm continues lumbering towards us. The prognosis
and updated forecasts. (McLachlin., Palm Beach Post). WITH MAP.
</P>
<P>
   WATER _ So it's going to flood. When, where and why. What
precautions are being taken by water managers? (King, Palm Beach
Post).
</P>
<P>
   RUSH _ MIAMI _ Officials in Miami-Dade were expected to begin
evacuations that could send millions of people north. Let the
gridlock begin. We chronicle how it will affect Palm Beach County.
(Desmon, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   KEYS _ THE FLORIDA KEYS _ Expected to be relatively quiet day in
the Keys as residents brace for the wrath of Georges. (Hiaasen in
Marathon, Staletovich in Key West and Kane in Key Largo, Plam Beach
Post).
</P>
<P>
   PREP _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Any last-minute stragglers for
supplies? (Bierman, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   ART _ So what if you didn't have just Target lawn furniture to
protect, you had priceless sculptures and paintings? That's exactly
the dilemma facing folks at the Norton Museum in West Palm Beach
and other museums. (Schwan, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
