<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    TV Preview for this weekend
 &HT;    By Bob Longino, Drew Jubera, Lyle V. Harris, and Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   THE NEW
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Two of a Kind'' 8 EDT tonight on ABC _ The return of
Mary-Kate and Ashley Olsen. At times they even talk alike. You
could lose your mind. But little viewers will love it. Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Buddy Faro'' 9 EDT tonight on CBS _ Dennis Farina as the
swingin' detective. Squaresville. Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Brother's Keeper'' 9:30 EDT tonight on ABC _ Viewers'
weeper. Grade: D
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Fantasy Island'' 9 p.m. EDT Saturday on ABC _ Not the Mr.
Roarke you remember. It's tales from the Dark Side. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Martial Law'' 9 p.m. EDT Saturday on CBS _ Sammo Hung plays
like Jackie Chan in an absurd cop chop thriller. And it beats the
stuffin' out of ``Walker, Texas Ranger.'' Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Cupid'' 10 p.m. EDT Saturday on ABC _ Jeremy Piven
(``Ellen'') is the god of love. Or is he? Grade: B+
</P>
<P>
   GOOD OLD FAVORITES
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Boy Meets World'' 8:30 EDT tonight on ABC _ Is it becoming
``Man Meets World?'' Cory's considering Topanga's proposal.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Sabrina, the Teenage Witch'' 9 EDT tonight on ABC _ The
third season begins with Sabrina, even with witch license in hand,
having to make a decision like a normal kid.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Homicide: Life on the Street'' 10 EDT tonight on NBC _
There are new faces. But we sure miss Andre Braugher. Grade: B-
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Nash Bridges'' 10 EDT tonight on CBS _ Nash winds up in hot
financial water.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Early Edition'' 8 p.m. EDT Saturday on CBS _ Oops. It's a
power blackout and Gary's got to avert disaster after disaster.
</P>
<P>
   PULL THE PLUG ALREADY
</P>
