<P>
   CLINTON-HOUSE (Washington) -- House Judiciary Committee chairman
says any information relevant to President Clinton's suitability
for office could be considered. By Bob Hohler. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-WOMEN (Washington) -- Women's groups say President
Clinton should not be impeached. While he did bad things, they say,
it could be even worse if more Republicans are elected to Congress.
By Mary Leonard. 1000 words
</P>
