</P>
<P>
   TV-RATINGS (Undated) -- The TV industry, which reluctantly
agreed one year ago to add rating labels to some programming, has
overwhelmingly failed to live up to its word, according to a new
study. By Don Aucoin. (a and e coding)
</P>
<P>
   MA-EPA-GE-PCB (Undated) -- The EPA is expected to announce a
deal with GE on the cleanup of PCB pollution in Pittsfield, Mass.,
ending years of negotiations and heading off a Superfund
designation. By Scott Allen and Peter Howe. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WALLST-BAILOUT (New York) -- Wall Street's extraordinary $300
billion bailout of one of the most prominent private investment
funds points up just how fragile the world economy has become. By
Peter G. Gosselin. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   VISAS-INCREASE (Washington) -- Congress and the White House
reach a deal to allow more foreign workers to take skilled jobs in
the United States, delighting high-tech companies and drawing
protests from labor groups. By Aaron Zitner. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
