   Fernandez appealed for international aid, calling the storm ``a
national tragedy.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Pray, and ask the Almighty to help the destiny of our
people,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   In Haiti, a desperately poor country of flimsy homes and a
fragile infrastructure, Georges killed 27 people and injured 29.
Many more were missing.
</P>
<P>
   The United Nations Development Program donated $100,000 for
disaster relief in Haiti, while the U.S. government donated water,
food, blankets, sheets, and clothing.
</P>
<P>
   In Puerto Rico, Georges inflicted an estimated $2 billion in
damages. Electricity was out across the U.S. territory of 3.8
million people, and service may not be restored in some places for
months.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
