<HEADLINE>
THE ART OF DIANNE FEINSTEIN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Known more for her political savvy than her creative impulses,
Senator  &UR; Dianne &LR;   &UR; Feinstein &LR;  has at last come out of the closet.
She is an artist.
</P>
<P>
   Avoiding subject matter _ ``The Scream'' or ``The Rape of the
Sabine Women,'' for instance _ that might have trite relevance to
government work, Feinstein concentrates on images from nature,
birds and flowers she's grown in her garden.
</P>
<P>
   The senator said she started drawing almost 10 years ago, &LR;  and
often doodles ``tulips, daisies and roses'' at meetings.
</P>
<P>
   She keeps the original of each formal work _ three birds and
seven flowers hang in her Washington office _ and uses framed
prints as donations to charitable causes or gifts to VIPs. Her work
has fetched as much as $2,000 at auction.
</P>
<P>
   Four Feinstein flower prints, &LR;  _ elegantly framed,
double-matted, signed and dated, &LR;  _ will be auctioned October 21 at
the ANA Hotel at the seventh annual Francis J. Curry Tribute Dinner
for the North of Market Senior Services.  &UR; Michael Krasny &LR;  is
keynote speaker. More information is available at (415) 885-2274.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LISTING THE PROS AND CONS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ More than 60 artists, intellectuals and just plain celebrities
have signed a petition, released in Paris on Wednesday, opposing
``inquisitorial harassment by a fanatical prosecutor with unlimited
power.''
</P>
<P>
   The anti-Starr petition, being circulated by former French
cultural minister  &UR; Jack Lang &LR; , was signed by Archbishop  &UR; Desmond &LR; 
 &UR; Tutu &LR;  of South Africa,  &UR; Gabriel Garcia Marquez &LR; ,  &UR; William Styron &LR; ,
 &UR; Carlos Fuentes &LR; ,  &UR; Gunter Grass &LR; ,  &UR; Gerard Depardieu &LR; ,  &UR; Vanessa &LR; 
 &UR; Redgrave &LR; ,  &UR; Emma Thompson &LR; ,  &UR; Anthony &LR;   &UR; Hopkins &LR; ,  &UR; Pierre Boulez &LR; ,
 &UR; Jessye Norman &LR; ,  &UR; Arthur Schlesinger Jr. &LR; ,  &UR; Jacques Derrida &LR; ,
 &UR; Lauren &LR; 
 &UR; Bacall &LR; ,  &UR; Claudia Cardinale &LR; ,  &UR; Alain Delon &LR; ,  &UR; Sophia Loren &LR; ,
 &UR; Charlotte Rampling &LR; ,  &UR; Liv Ullmann &LR; ,  &UR; Art Garfunkel &LR; ,  &UR; Bernardo &LR; 
 &UR; Bertolucci &LR; ,  &UR; Wim Wenders &LR; ,  &UR; Robert Altman &LR; ,  &UR; Jane Campion &LR;  and
 &UR; Constantin Costa-Gavras &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   ``A statesman is answerable to public opinion or to the law only
for his public acts,'' said a portion of the statement quoted in
the Washington Post. ``All else is solely a matter of his own
conscience.''
</P>
<P>
   _ ``How many women has he slept with?'' asks the latest issue of
Glamour magazine, which was referring to any woman's boyfriend. (A
hundred before he was 40,  &UR; Monica Lewinsky &LR;  told
 &UR; Kenneth Starr &LR; , but ``Solomon'' had 300 concubines,  &UR; Bill Burke &LR; 
read in some Philharmonia Baroque program notes.)
</P>
<P>
   A survey of 200 American men 18 to 45 years old found the
maximum number of lovers was ``between 40 and 50,'' a total
accumulated by a man who said he lied to some women about it ``when
it was clear they'd be appalled by the truth.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Beyond your first few partners,'' said  &UR; Richard Kadrey &LR; ,
former editor of a sex magazine, ``there's something kind of
adolescent about counting. At first, you need to prove to yourself
that you can get laid, but after a while, you're just keeping
score.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jerry Oppenheimer &LR; , who trashed  &UR; Martha Stewart &LR;  in a
best-seller published last year, is writing ``State of a Union,'' a
book about &UR; Bill &LR;  and  &UR; Hillary Clinton &LR; 's marriage, for
HarperCollins.
</P>
<P>
   Oppenheimer doesn't seem to have any special inside knowledge of
this relationship, but his agent,  &UR; Joni Evans &LR; , told Publisher's
Weekly that he ``knows how to ask the right questions, then he
prints the answers.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Bawang &LR;  the western lowland gorilla gave birth at the San
Francisco Zoo on Wednesday. Members of the gorilla family were
allowed to be with the mother during the birth.
</P>
<P>
   Weight and gender of the infant are unknown, &LR;  because the
newborn is clinging so tightly to Bawang.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Making these horror movies isn't as easy as it might look.
You're trying to act, and there's all these damn puppeteers
crawling around under your feet.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Jennifer Tilly, who stars in the forthcoming movie ``Bride of
Chucky,'' in TV Guide Online.
</P>
</TEXT>
