 TIJUANA: from prison.  
<TEXT>
<P>
   According to American law enforcement documents, the Monges were
convicted on drug charges in 1995 and deported to Mexico after
crossing into the United States in cars loaded with marijuana.
</P>
<P>
   But the Baja state judge who is trying the kidnapping case said
the drug arrest records of the supposed kidnapping victims had
little bearing on the case.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not here to rule on the conduct of the kidnapping
victims, only the conduct of the accused kidnappers,'' the judge,
Blanca Estela Avalos Favela, said in an interview.
</P>
<P>
   The agents' arrest comes days after United States-Mexican
relations over narcotics matters were strained by two other reports
of top-level corruption in Mexican law enforcement units.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't intervene _ its not our deal,'' said an American
official speaking on the condition of anonymity. ``But what kind of
message does this send to these guys? The first little thing they
do, they're in jail.'' &QL;
</P>
