<SLUG> BC-WOMEN-LESLIE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Female pros can beat the average guy
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lisa Leslie, 26, is one of the marquee players in the WNBA and
has used her athletic ability and glamorous appearance to moonlight
as a model. The Los Angeles Sparks center talks about playing
against male basketball players.
</P>
<P>
   Men are just naturally stronger. Their muscles are going to be
stronger than ours. That doesn't mean they're better players,
unless you're talking about the elite athlete or the professional
player. The average man, unless he's really been working on his
game, your female professional can most likely beat playing
basketball _ whether one on one or in a pickup game.
</P>
<P>
   As far as the NBA guys, we can compete with all of them, but I
don't know that we'd necessarily win. We're not going to go out on
the court and beat them in a five-on-five game. I can just speak
from my experience playing in the summer with the guys.
</P>
<P>
   It's tough, but you have be ready to body up with them, elbow
them, push them around. But basically, I try to beat them down the
floor, run the floor and work on technique.
</P>
<P>
   They'll say, ``Lisa, you run the floor like Scottie Pippen.'' As
soon as the shot goes up, I'm down the floor, because I know I
can't go one on one with them in the post. So I'm going to step
outside and shoot a jumper.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
