NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, SEPTEMBER 25
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on
</P>
<P>
   BC-PAKISTAN-U.N.-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Sept. 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Sept.
23, about Pakistan's offer to sign the treaty banning nuclear
weapons tests referred incorrectly to the status of the treaty in
the United States. President Clinton has indeed sent it to the
Senate for ratification.
</P>
<P>
   BC-FED-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Sept. 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Sept.
23, about remarks by Alan Greenspan, chairman of the Federal
Reserve, referred incorrectly to the 257.21-point gain in the Dow
Jones industrial average that day. It was not the strongest advance
since Aug. 31; the strongest was 380.53 points on Sept. 8.
Wednesday's close of 8,154.41 was the Dow's highest close since
Aug. 31.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SHADRACH-FILM-REVIEW-NYT (moved on Tuesday, September 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, September
22, about a film review of ``Shadrach'' misidentified the
characters played by Andie MacDowell and Deborah Hedwall. It is Ms.
MacDowell who plays ``the beer-swilling, warmhearted mother,''
Trixie Dabney. Ms. Hedwall, whose character is referred to as
Mother in the film, plays the mother of another character,
10-year-old Paul Whitehurst.
</P>
</TEXT>
