<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    PAX TV special features book on biblical 'secrets'
 &HT;    By Marguerite M. Plunkett
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. -- PAX TV will air an original special,
Secrets of Bible Code Revealed, based on a book that claims the
Bible includes buried information on events of the past, present
and future.
</P>
<P>
   The West Palm Beach-based network, which parent Paxson
Communications (AMEX: PAX, $9.75) launched last month, will air the
two-hour special from 8 p.m. to 10 p.m. Oct. 30, according to
Paxson.
</P>
<P>
   The company declined to reveal how much the special would cost.
Producers are Chuck Sellier and Dave Balsiger of Grizzly Adams
Productions, spokeswoman Lea Sloan said.
</P>
<P>
   The special explores the ``revelations'' from Michael Drosnin's
best-selling book, The Bible Code, according to a Paxson release.
It will ``inform, inspire and entertain viewers of all ages,
allowing them to form their own opinions,'' said Bill Scott, Paxson
programming president.
</P>
<P>
   Drosnin's book says the original Hebrew text of the first five
books of the Bible gives the names of rabbis who lived centuries
later as well as modern-day assassinations when decoded by
computer.
</P>
<P>
   It foretells events, including the assassination of President
John F. Kennedy and Sen. Robert F. Kennedy, plus the circumstances
surrounding the death of Princess Diana, according to the Paxson
release.
</P>
<P>
   PAX is built on a foundation of rerun programming including
Touched by an Angel, Diagnosis Murder and Dr. Quinn, Medicine
Woman. The network runs Worship programming overnight, which shows
images of nature run while running scripture.
</P>
<P>
   The programming is distributed on 95 owned, operated and
affiliated stations as well as cable throughout the country.
WPXP-Channel 67 is Paxson's West Palm Beach station.
</P>
