<TEXT>
<P>
   The following story is an added starter on The New York Times
front page. It will replace CLINTON-CONGRESS on the page. We plan
to move story by 12 a.m., ET.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-JONES (Washington) _ Lawyers for Paula Jones said on
Thursday they are engaged in serious discussions with the
president's lawyers about reaching a financial settlement to end
her sexual-misconduct lawsuit, which set off the events that has
led to the possible impeachment action against Clinton. By Neil A.
Lewis.
